text: I am devastated at the news two of our brave, serving ADF personnel lost their lives today when their army vehicle rolled over near Townsville.  Wherever the sacrifice of our brave men and women of our ADF occurs, it is a great price for them to pay, all in equal measure.

text: Deeply saddened to hear of the passing of Senator Alex Gallacher. He proudly served in our Parliament for 10 years & we thank him for that wonderful service to his country. My deepest condolences go to his family, friends & colleagues & those in the Labor movement. May he RIP.
english: Deeply saddened to hear of the passing of Senator Alex Gallacher. He proudly served in our Parliament for 10 years & we thank him for that wonderful service to his country. My deepest condolences go to his family, friends & colleagues & those in the Labor movement. May he RIP.

text: Australia continues to lead the world in our comeback from the #COVID19 global pandemic and recession. Our economy grew 1.8% in the March quarter - outperforming G7 economies. According to @ABSStats, our economy has now recovered to be above pre-pandemic levels. https://t.co/wRcj6xrtBl
english: Australia continues to lead the world in our comeback from the #COVID19 global pandemic and recession. Our economy grew 1.8% in the March quarter - outperforming G7 economies. According to @ABSStats, our economy has now recovered to be above pre-pandemic levels. https://t.co/wRcj6xrtBl

text: Great calls with Kiribati President Maamau, PNG PM Marape & Solomon Islands PM Sogavare. We discussed Australia’s steadfast support for the health & resilience of our Pacific family as they respond to #COVID19, infrastructure support, labour mobility & shared security interests.
english: Great calls with Kiribati President Maamau, PNG PM Marape & Solomon Islands PM Sogavare. We discussed Australia’s steadfast support for the health & resilience of our Pacific family as they respond to #COVID19, infrastructure support, labour mobility & shared security interests.

text: Delighted to speak with Vietnamese PM Chinh tonight. Australia & Vietnam are close strategic partners, with thriving trade & investment ties. We’ll continue to work together on shared challenges in the Indo-Pacific, bilaterally & through Australia’s close cooperation with ASEAN.
english: Delighted to speak with Vietnamese PM Chinh tonight. Australia & Vietnam are close strategic partners, with thriving trade & investment ties. We’ll continue to work together on shared challenges in the Indo-Pacific, bilaterally & through Australia’s close cooperation with ASEAN.

text: A record 101,146 doses of #COVID19 vaccines were administered in Australia in past 24 hours, bringing the total administered to nearly 3.5 million. Our vaccination program continues to ramp up. I encourage everyone to roll up their sleeves and get their jab when it’s their turn.
english: A record 101,146 doses of #COVID19 vaccines were administered in Australia in past 24 hours, bringing the total administered to nearly 3.5 million. Our vaccination program continues to ramp up. I encourage everyone to roll up their sleeves and get their jab when it’s their turn.

text: With unemployment falling to 5.5%, 33,800 more full time jobs being created and youth unemployment down to the lowest level since 2009, our plan to secure Australia’s recovery is working.
english: With unemployment falling to 5.5%, 33,800 more full time jobs being created and youth unemployment down to the lowest level since 2009, our plan to secure Australia’s recovery is working.

text: Thank you to all the nurses across Australia for the amazing job you do. You have been on the front line of this global #COVID19 pandemic, helping to protect Australians and caring for our communities. Happy #InternationalNursesDay! #IND2021 https://t.co/UlU8MiyY5Y
english: Thank you to all the nurses across Australia for the amazing job you do. You have been on the front line of this global #COVID19 pandemic, helping to protect Australians and caring for our communities. Happy #InternationalNursesDay! #IND2021 https://t.co/UlU8MiyY5Y

text: Australia is now well on the road to recovery.  #Budget2021 secures our recovery and sets Australia up for the future.
english: Australia is now well on the road to recovery.  #Budget2021 secures our recovery and sets Australia up for the future.

text: Our Government has nearly doubled spending on mental health since we came to office.  It is a clear national priority. #Budget2021 extends our support even further with a $2.3 billion commitment to mental health care and suicide prevention. https://t.co/vkTzW4UxX6
english: Our Government has nearly doubled spending on mental health since we came to office.  It is a clear national priority. #Budget2021 extends our support even further with a $2.3 billion commitment to mental health care and suicide prevention. https://t.co/vkTzW4UxX6

text: #Budget2021 delivers $17.7 billion in practical and targeted new funding to significantly improve the aged care system.   It’s about ensuring older Australians are treated with respect, care and dignity.
english: #Budget2021 delivers $17.7 billion in practical and targeted new funding to significantly improve the aged care system.   It’s about ensuring older Australians are treated with respect, care and dignity.

text: Around 250,000 families will now have access to more affordable childcare and will be better off by an average of $2200 a year, thanks to a $1.7 billion investment in #Budget2021. It focuses on low and middle income families, enabling more parents to get back to work.
english: Around 250,000 families will now have access to more affordable childcare and will be better off by an average of $2200 a year, thanks to a $1.7 billion investment in #Budget2021. It focuses on low and middle income families, enabling more parents to get back to work.

text: #Budget2021 doubles our Government’s commitment to the JobTrainer fund.  Supporting a total of over 450,000 new training places to upskill job seekers and young people.  We want to equip Australians with the skills they need to get a job today and tomorrow. https://t.co/obH2YE8Sij
english: #Budget2021 doubles our Government’s commitment to the JobTrainer fund.  Supporting a total of over 450,000 new training places to upskill job seekers and young people.  We want to equip Australians with the skills they need to get a job today and tomorrow. https://t.co/obH2YE8Sij

text: Over 10 million hard-working Australians will benefit from a new and additional tax cut in #Budget2021.  Low & middle-income earners will receive up to $1,080 for individuals or $2,160 for couples.  More of their money in their pockets to spend across the economy, creating jobs.
english: Over 10 million hard-working Australians will benefit from a new and additional tax cut in #Budget2021.  Low & middle-income earners will receive up to $1,080 for individuals or $2,160 for couples.  More of their money in their pockets to spend across the economy, creating jobs.

text: Australia is coming back. Our plan is working and our economic engine is roaring back to life.   Since the last Budget, more than half a million jobs have been created and more Australians are now in work than ever before.  #Budget2021 #auspol
english: Australia is coming back. Our plan is working and our economic engine is roaring back to life.   Since the last Budget, more than half a million jobs have been created and more Australians are now in work than ever before.  #Budget2021 #auspol

text: #Budget2021 is our plan to secure Australia’s economic recovery and build for the future.  A plan that continues to protect Australians from COVID.  A plan that creates more jobs and guarantees essential services.  A plan that builds a more resilient and secure Australia.
english: #Budget2021 is our plan to secure Australia’s economic recovery and build for the future.  A plan that continues to protect Australians from COVID.  A plan that creates more jobs and guarantees essential services.  A plan that builds a more resilient and secure Australia.

text: Just spoke with our friend, PM @narendramodi who thanked Australia for standing by India during the #COVID19 crisis. We’re supporting them with ventilators and oxygen concentrators. We won’t forget India’s generosity in exporting vaccines. We’ll work closely on global challenges.
english: Just spoke with our friend, PM @narendramodi who thanked Australia for standing by India during the #COVID19 crisis. We’re supporting them with ventilators and oxygen concentrators. We won’t forget India’s generosity in exporting vaccines. We’ll work closely on global challenges.

text: In the Hunter to announce a jobs boom. #Budget2021 delivers $66m to make the @NTLairport upgrade happen, with work to start in August. That’ll deliver 4,400 new jobs & thousands of extra tourists to the region, spending money in local businesses ➡️ https://t.co/pu6LH653Oi https://t.co/whnnnDcrGM

text: Congrats to Tasmanian Premier Peter Gutwein & the @TasLiberal team. While votes are still being counted, under Peter’s strong, calm & cooperative leadership they have continued to take the State forward. Thanks to all Tasmanians for their support of the Liberal Team in Tasmania.
english: Congrats to Tasmanian Premier Peter Gutwein & the @TasLiberal team. While votes are still being counted, under Peter’s strong, calm & cooperative leadership they have continued to take the State forward. Thanks to all Tasmanians for their support of the Liberal Team in Tasmania.
